title: more ch2 typos
body:
Hi, 

Here are some more recommendationsI found. Is it easier to have 1 long list, or split into separate ~5 change requests?

1) I think "rigourous" is not a real word. Did a quick Google search
org: We are not aware of any rigourous work done
chg: We are not aware of any **rigorous** work done

2) added a "w", and also fixed the link
org: they have as this book as written
chg: they have **was** this book as written

org: on the http://book.fast.ai[book website]
on the **[book website](http://book.fast.ai)**

3) stretch -> stretched, and added an as
org: If we squished or stretch the images then they end up unrealistic shapes,
chg: If we squished or **stretched** the images then they end up **as** unrealistic shapes,

4) "to" to "on"
org: To tell fastai we want to use these transforms to a batch
chg: To tell fastai we want to use these transforms **on** a batch

Regards,
Daniel Lam

title: more ch2 chgs
body:
Hello, here are some recommendations:

1) added "the"
org: how loss is calculated and used in training process
chg: how loss is calculated and used in **the** training process

2) typo, predicitions -> predictions

3) matching plurals (reasons). there's -> there are
org: There's a few reasons for this:
chg: There **are** a few reasons for this

4) matching plurals (reasons). there is -> there are
org: There is quite a few upsides to this approach. 
chg: There are quite a few upsides to this approach. 

5) Two changes.
i) org: ... building not only the models (fun!) but infrastructure to ensure ...
i) chg: ... building not only the models (fun!) but **also the** infrastructure to ensure ...

ii) org: ... what you personally find it easy to do.
ii) chg: ... what you personally find **is** easy to do.

title: ch 4 recommendations
body:
1) add "to"
org : we will use calculate a metric
chg : we will use **to** calculate a metric

2) There's -> There are
org: There's a couple of important points
chg: There **are** a couple of important points

3) Split run-on sentence into two complete sentences
org: This is just a performance optimisation, we would get exactly the same results
chg: This is just a performance optimisation**. W**e would get exactly the same results

4) a -> an
org: using a *optimiser step*
chg: using **an** *optimiser step*

5) space -> speed
org: You want to build a model of how the space changes over time.
chg: You want to build a model of how the **speed** changes over time.

6) "that we feed" -> "and feed them"
org: To do this, we take a few data items (such as images) that we feed to our model.
chg: To do this, we take a few data items (such as images) **and feed them** to our model.

7) peak -> peek
org: in your excitement to peak under the hood?
chg: in your excitement to **peek** under the hood?
